<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 7:06PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Anson,
southeastern Montgomery and northwestern Richmond Counties through
745 PM EDT...
At 706 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadesboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Ansonville, Mount Gilead, Ellerbe, Lilesville, Norman,
Blewett Falls Lake, Derby, Covington and Pekin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
